        <h2>Diabetes Treatments</h2>
        <p>
            There is currently no cure for diabetes, but all hope is not lost as they can be treated and controlled if you put in the effort. Treatment for diabetes depends on what type you have but a general rule of thumb that will make it easier to manage is:

        </p>
        <br>
        <ul>
            <li>Eating healthy. Focus on including more fruits, vegetables, proteins, and whole grains into your diet whilst limiting foods that are high in saturated fats and carbohydrates.</li>
            <br><li>Exercising daily. Exercise lowers your blood glucose levels by using up the sugar in your blood as energy. It increases your sensitivity on insulin meaning your body needs less of it to export the glucose into your cells. Exercise doesn't have to be a chore, choose an activity that you enjoy whether it be cycling, swimming, or boxing. Just make sure you do it daily!</li>
        </ul>
